      • report

        public void report(MeasurementUnit measurementUnit)
            throws ReportingException
        Reports a newly measured MeasurementUnit. Each Measurement Unit must be reported exactly once.
        Parameters:
        measurementUnit - A MeasurementUnit to be reported.
        Throws:
        ReportingException - If reporting could not be done properly.

      • reset

        public void reset()
        Resets reporting to the zero state. It is used after the warm-up period.

      • registerReporter

      • getReporters

        public Set<Reporter> getReporters()
        Gets an immutable list of current reporters.
        Returns:
        An immutable list of currently registered reporters.

      • start

        public void start()
        Starts the reporting facility.

      • stop

        public void stop()
        Stops the reporting facility. It must not be called sooner than all SenderTasks have been completed.
